Note: I found out about this through some convoluted static declaration in Java which was only hit in a few small cases in pytest tests. The symptom was that if I ran one of these special python tests (with the ``-k`` flag to pytest for instance), I was able to see that pytest ran everything as expected, even reporting the final results, but never actually terminated (so it just sat there without returning the prompt after running the tests). My first instinct was that this was another signal handler issue (e.g. #813) but couldn't find anything relevant in PyTest. As you can see, it turned out to be a complete red-herring, which I might not have fallen for with an relevant entry in the CHANGELOG. Hence the issue :wink:.

